-- India to Buy Back 120 Billion Rupees of 2010 Bonds on October 25, RBI Says
-- B y   V .   R a m a k r i s h n a n
-- 2010-10-22T02:48:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/india-to-buy-back-120-billion-rupees-of-2010-bonds-on-october-25-rbi-says.html
India plans to buy back 120 billion
rupees ($2.7 billion) of bonds maturing this year and next
through an auction on Oct. 25, the  central bank  said in an e-
mailed statement yesterday.  The move is part of plans to buy back a combined 285.5
billion rupees of bonds maturing in 2010 and 2011, which was
announced by the finance ministry earlier yesterday.  The government plans to purchase the 8.75 percent, 2010
note and the 12.32 percent, 2011 debt, according to the central
bank statement. It will also offer to buy 6.57 percent notes due
next year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
V. Ramakrishnan in Mumbai at 
 rvenkatarama@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sandy Hendry at 
 shendry@bloomberg.net . 